data.title: Wellington
data.text:
Tonight

Showers and thunderstorms likely, mainly between 2am and 3am. Some of the storms could produce heavy rainfall. Increasing clouds, with a low around 73. South southeast wind 8 to 10 mph becoming north after midnight. Winds could gust as high as 21 mph. Chance of precipitation is 70%. New rainfall amounts between a half and three quarters of an inch possible.

Thursday

A chance of showers and thunderstorms before 10am, then a chance of showers and thunderstorms after 1pm. Cloudy through mid morning, then gradual clearing, with a high near 91. Heat index values as high as 102. South wind 7 to 9 mph becoming west southwest in the afternoon. Winds could gust as high as 20 mph. Chance of precipitation is 40%. New rainfall amounts between a tenth and quarter of an inch, except higher amounts possible in thunderstorms.
